The Hong Kong government said on Sunday that it will slaughter all chickens in local chicken farms and all poultry at wholesale markets and retail outlets in an attempt to get rid of the source of influenza A H5N1 virus or "bird flu".
The Central Government and relevant departments in Guangdong Province have tightened quarantine controls and offered active assistance to Hong Kong in the battle against bird flu.
Macao is fully prepared for any possible outbreak of the bird flu although no case of H5N1 virus has been found a doctor with the Government Hospital said.
